cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.COM
Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the optimization of a mesh network for cellular communication. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper formulates an optimization problem to maximize the minimum end-to-end per user data rate. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with millimeter wave cellular networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper considers both integrated access-backhaul (IAB) and orthogonal access-backhaul (OAB) resource allocation strategies. 
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper provides design guidelines for the implementation of millimeter wave cellular networks.
